{"author":{"id":"c36a84ec98218e4306bb41a3682590396070437d3c9a5a205cf08b57e923d5bf"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1698652622,"nonce":"fz18XwiExdrlig+XBU0Oe8muKXo=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s51SRduzk0T-a4"},"target":"f1898e38330c4c2f98e8473e3c88413742d10c5b9e2fd3f8387b50b47d4c3e78","message":"Currently, the DESeq2 does not call `lfcShrink` for shrinkage of fold changes (FCs). Instead, it uses the `betaPrior=True` of `DESeq` function which was an old practice before `lfcShrink` was introduced in v1.16.  The current approach should also shrink the FCs but the following DE analysis also takes the `betaPrior` option into account.  The vignette suggests using FC shrinkage for visualization and ranking. Hence, running `DESeq` function with `betaPrior=FALSE` followed by `lfcShrink` function should reproduce the vignette. The results tabular file should be the result of `DESeq` function. The results of `lfcShrink` should be used for MA plots. I hope the p-values do not change after `lfcShrink` (only the FCs are changed). This has to be tested. So it would be nice to have an option to choose the results tabular from `lfcShrink` output to have shrunk FCs in the output.\n\nFor further pre-discussion on this issue please refer to this PR: https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/5294","files":null}]}